remarks.para:
The recommended implementation pattern is:
[FormatItem] internal string CellsStr { [MethodImpl(MethodImplOptions.AggressiveInlining)] get => Cells.ToString(); }
You can use the code snippet fitem to create the pattern, whose corresponding file is added into the optional/vssnippets folder. For more information, please open the markdown file README.md (in the optional folder) for more information.

If you want to use the values in the resource documents,
just use the  field  is okay:

using static Sudoku.Resources.MergedResources;

public override string Format => R["TheKeyYouWantToSearch"];

member.param:
The handler method that used for the invocation on output the result information.
For example, the following code is okay for this argument:

PrintInferences(
    // Suppose we output the strong inference dictionary.
    inferences: _strongInferences,

    // Here we can call 'Console.WriteLine' to output the result string value.
    // In addition, you can also write 'static data => Console.WriteLine(data)'.
    outputHandler: Console.WriteLine
);

summary.para:
If you want to check the resource, please use the indexer  to get them.
The return value of the indexer is ?:

using static Sudoku.Resources.MergedResources;

string? resourceValue = R["SuchKeyYouWantToSearchFor"];
if (resourceValue is not null)
{
    // Insert the arbitrary code using 'resourceValue'.
}
